lead_paragraph: SCHECHTER--<PERSON>Aaron</PERSON>, born on <DATE>March 19, 1926</DATE> in <LOCATION>Brooklyn</LOCATION>, NY passed away peacefully in <LOCATION>New York</LOCATION> on <DATE>December 22nd</DATE>. Aaron had a wonderful life with no regrets; to quote <PERSON>Frank Sinatra</PERSON>, I did it my way. An entertainment CPA, hand holder and most importantly a genuinely nice man for his career of sixty-five plus years. His wife, <PERSON>Elaine</PERSON>, served as his right hand through it all. They had an unshakeable bond that later generations hope to emulate. He leaves his wife, <PERSON>Elaine Abrams</PERSON> and three wonderful daughters --<PERSON>Annie Kasper Tom</PERSON>, <PERSON>Sarah Gill Tony</PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION>Betsy Waters Andrew</ORGANIZATION> along with the great joys of his life --<PERSON>Rebecca</PERSON>, <PERSON>Caroline</PERSON> and <PERSON>Priscilla Kasper</PERSON>, <PERSON>Maxwell</PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION>Sammy Waters</ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON>Oliver Gill</PERSON>. He often quipped; We should have had the grandchildren first. Also survived by his sailing buddies <PERSON>Ellen</PERSON> and <PERSON>Marty Abrams</PERSON>, brother <PERSON>Mike Shepherd</PERSON>, <PERSON>Alex Rooks</PERSON> and <PERSON>Jules Alexander</PERSON> and their families. In <DATE>2000</DATE>, after enjoying <LOCATION>Compo Beach</LOCATION> in <LOCATION>Westport</LOCATION>, CT for thirty-seven years, <PERSON>Aaron</PERSON> and <PERSON>Elaine</PERSON> returned to <LOCATION>Manhattan</LOCATION> where he enjoyed his backyard, <LOCATION>Central Park</LOCATION>, as a visitor and volunteer. Donations in his honor may be made to the <PERSON>Aaron Schechter Baruch</PERSON> College Scholarship Fund, c/o Baruch College Fund, One <PERSON>Bernard Baruch Way</PERSON>, Box A-1063, NY NY 10010. A memorial celebration will be held on <DATE>Friday January 30, 2015</DATE> at 6pm at the <ORGANIZATION>Baruch Performing Arts Center Nagelberg Theater</ORGANIZATION>. Entrance on south side East 25th Street between Third and Lex. Bowtie Optional. 1/3
